{"TopicId":181629,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Does Commnet allow multihop connections?","CreatedByName":"iFlyAllTheTime","CreatedById":111190,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T21:07:40Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"iFlyAllTheTime","CreatedById":111190,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T21:07:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m away on business for a couple of weeks so I can\u0027t test this out on my PC but I\u0027ve been thinking of a mission outline that relies on proper usage of Commnet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet\u0027s say I have:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\na rover on Ike with a Communotron 16 (Ike surface facing away from Duna, but in LoS of Ike relay),\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\na 2 satellite highly elliptical relay with HG-5 around Ike (no LoS to Kerbin but LoS to Duna relay) , and\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\na 3 satellite equatorial relay with RA-15 or RA-100 around Duna (LoS to Ike relay and Kerbin)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDoes the default \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommnet\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E allow the rover on Ike to be controlled on the surface, with the signal bouncing from Kerbin--\u0026gt;Duna relay--\u0026gt;Ike relay--\u0026gt;Ike rover?\u003C/strong\u003E Or do I need to have a relay in Ike orbit capable of reaching Kerbin?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s what I quickly threw together to illustrate my question:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022uTz2z9v.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022451\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/uTz2z9v.png\u0022 width=\u0022934\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a side note, would Remotetech allow this connection (\u003Cem\u003Esignal from point A to B to C \u003C/em\u003E\u003Cem\u003Eand\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cem\u003E then finally to D, or even further to E\u003C/em\u003E), given the appropriate omni and dish antennae?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T21:09:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527613\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181629\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548277660\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111190\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022iFlyAllTheTime\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, iFlyAllTheTime said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDoes the default \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommnet\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E allow the rover on Ike to be controlled on the surface, with the signal bouncing from Kerbin--\u0026gt;Duna relay--\u0026gt;Ike relay--\u0026gt;Ike rover?\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup, hop all you want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoatRider","CreatedById":103681,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-23T21:10:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll the hops need to be \u0022Relay\u0022 and not \u0022Direct\u0022. And the weakest link will be the link of the connection at the end.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-25T01:25:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223527613\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181629\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548277660\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111190\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022iFlyAllTheTime\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/23/2019 at 1:07 PM, iFlyAllTheTime said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EDoes the default \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommnet\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E allow the rover on Ike to be controlled on the surface, with the signal bouncing from Kerbin--\u0026gt;Duna relay--\u0026gt;Ike relay--\u0026gt;Ike rover?\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes.\u00A0 That is, indeed, the whole \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Epoint\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E of the \u0022relay\u0022 antennas in KSP. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean, if multi-hop wasn\u0027t a thing, there wouldn\u0027t be any distinction between a relay antenna like the RA-100 and a direct antenna like the Communotron 88-88.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"iFlyAllTheTime","CreatedById":111190,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-25T16:35:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223528396\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181629\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548379546\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125662\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Snark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, Snark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes.\u00A0 That is, indeed, the whole \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Epoint\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E of the \u0022relay\u0022 antennas in KSP. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean, if multi-hop wasn\u0027t a thing, there wouldn\u0027t be any distinction between a relay antenna like the RA-100 and a direct antenna like the Communotron 88-88.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blush:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_embarrassed.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:blush:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know why but I was incorrectly thinking the range calculation only ever takes into account your current vessel and another one, which needs to be a relay. So I didn\u0027t think that that relay would be able to connect to a third relay, which then connects to Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: On a side-note, any idea why I cannot hit the \u0022Like\u0022 button on posts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-25T16:44:06Z\u0022 title=\u002201/25/2019 04:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 25, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by iFlyAllTheTime\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoatRider","CreatedById":103681,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-25T18:08:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck out this 6 hop relay to my lander on Pol:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022NFUgWOW.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022628\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/NFUgWOW.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pecan","CreatedById":96332,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-25T20:57:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223528676\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181629\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548434155\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111190\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022iFlyAllTheTime\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, iFlyAllTheTime said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn a side-note, any idea why I cannot hit the \u0022Like\u0022 button on posts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo much love.\u00A0 (You can only \u0027like\u0027 a certain number of things per day and have probably reached your limit)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"iFlyAllTheTime","CreatedById":111190,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-26T06:18:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223528751\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181629\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548439712\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103681\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GoatRider\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/25/2019 at 1:08 PM, GoatRider said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck out this 6 hop relay to my lander on Pol:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/NFUgWOW.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022NFUgWOW.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022628\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/NFUgWOW.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is glorious!\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t wait to launch the network and the rover!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for screenshot \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223528878\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181629\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548449830\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002296332\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pecan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/25/2019 at 3:57 PM, Pecan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo much love.\u00A0 (You can only \u0027like\u0027 a certain number of things per day and have probably reached your limit)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYay! I was able to! Maybe it was just the browser...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nanywho... Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdit